# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you
#   use pyenv and want other developers to use the same version of Python
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if Pipfile.lock is not desired, uncomment the following line.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv and Poetry, pdm.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#.pdm.toml
#.pdm-plugins/
#.pdm-build/

# PEP 582; project packages directory (e.g. pdm)
__pypackages__/

